Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.23,0:00:21.91,kyohaku,,0000,0283,0255,,{\fnMyriad Web Pro\b1\fs70\bord2\blur2\c&H000000&\fad(500,0)}June Bride
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.53,0:00:03.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A June bride.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.59,0:00:06.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As "June," the English word for the sixth month,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.08,0:00:10.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,comes from Juno, the guardian of marriage in Roman mythology,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.95,0:00:15.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,brides who marry in June are known to become happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.69,0:00:21.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Today, we'll revisit that case where a bride looking forward to happiness faces a tragedy!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.26,0:00:25.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The rhythm of the piano makes the flowers bloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.12,0:00:26.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The couple facing each other is a mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.92,0:00:30.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As she wishes upon lemon tea,\Nher snow white dress is stained in red!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.25,0:00:32.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.85,0:00:34.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,With the body of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.89,0:00:37.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,500)}His name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.25,0:02:29.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Today, a middle school teacher that Ran and I had is getting married.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.72,0:02:33.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm definitely not here for her sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.39,0:02:37.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted to see\Nthe wacko who's marrying her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.07,0:02:42.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Matsumoto-sensei... I haven't seen her since we graduated!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.84,0:02:46.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we'll get to hear her amazing singing voice at the reception!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.97,0:02:49.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, what about you-know-who?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.38,0:02:51.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, the kid who\Nwould always get yelled at
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.61,0:02:54.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,being off key in\NMatsumoto-sensei's music class...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.75,0:02:57.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.28,0:02:59.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I called him but he said wouldn't go even if his life depended on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.82,0:03:03.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you brought this kid with you instead of Mr. Tone-Deaf?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.18,0:03:06.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep! He insisted on coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.62,0:03:09.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me for being tone-deaf!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.42,0:03:13.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That lousy woman did nothing but torture me for three full years!
Dialogue: 1,0:03:17.09,0:03:21.55,Character Card,,0000,0000,0060,,{\fad(400,0)}{\fs36}Sayuri Matsumoto (27)\N{\fs30}Teitan Middle School\NMusic Teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.09,0:03:21.55,Character Card,,0000,0000,0050,,{\fad(0,0)\fscx98.75\fscy147.5\clip(326,547,640,674)\c&HBD4951&}m 0 0 l -36 0 l -36 0 l -36 11 l -36 13 l 0 13 m -22 -11 m -44 -35
Dialogue: 2,0:03:18.54,0:03:22.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Mouri-san and Suzuki-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.84,0:03:26.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Does it look good on me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.42,0:03:28.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You look beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.35,0:03:30.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-She does...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.90,0:03:31.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.76,0:03:35.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have we met before, little boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.98,0:03:37.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.12,0:03:40.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Look this way, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.83,0:03:43.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in charge of the video for today!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.37,0:03:45.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure the kiss scene is a really great one!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.54,0:03:47.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to me!
Dialogue: 1,0:03:48.29,0:03:51.96,Character Card,,0100,0000,0075,,{\fad(400,0)}{\fs36}Kazumi Takenaka (27)\N{\fs30}Close friend of Sayuri
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.29,0:03:51.96,Character Card,,0000,0000,0050,,{\fad(0,0)\fscx98.75\fscy147.5\c&HBD4951&\clip(355,544,668,676)}m 0 0 l -36 0 l -36 0 l -36 11 l -36 13 l 0 13 m -22 -11 m -44 -35
Dialogue: 2,0:03:48.11,0:03:51.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bought you your warm lemon tea, Sayuri!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.82,0:03:54.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.17,0:03:57.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, she was always drinking lemon tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.53,0:03:59.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even during class...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.88,0:04:05.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Your lipstick will come off if you drink it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.76,0:04:08.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.86,0:04:09.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.77,0:04:16.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazumi... I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.61,0:04:18.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,About Toshihiko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.56,0:04:21.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about at a time like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.53,0:04:23.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You better be ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.21,0:04:27.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna tell everyone at the reception that your new hubby used to be my boyfriend!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.63,0:04:28.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.36,0:04:32.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.09,0:04:34.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See you in a little bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.21,0:04:36.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She never stops teasing me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.35,0:04:38.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.02,0:04:39.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A bad friend of mine from college.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.67,0:04:43.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I have another can,\Nwould one of you like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.23,0:04:45.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, I'll take it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.53,0:04:53.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.40,0:04:55.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran! Beat this gorilla's brains out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.13,0:04:58.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? If it isn't Ran-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.12,0:05:00.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure!\NWhat are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.38,0:05:04.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who in their right mind would miss their boss's daughter's wedding?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.53,0:05:05.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Boss?
Dialogue: 1,0:05:08.78,0:05:12.04,Character Card,,0055,0000,0060,,{\fad(400,0)}{\fs36}Kiyonaga Matsumoto (54)\N{\fs30}Tokyo Police Superintendent\NSayuri's Father
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.78,0:05:12.04,Character Card,,0000,0000,0050,,{\fad(0,0)\fscx98.75\fscy147.5\c&HBD4951&\clip(313,545,663,678)}m 0 0 l -36 0 l -36 0 l -36 11 l -36 13 l 0 13 m -22 -11 m -44 -35
Dialogue: 2,0:05:05.96,0:05:10.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. He's the police\N superintendent... and my father!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.04,0:05:13.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.33,0:05:16.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.62,0:05:18.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.84,0:05:20.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please forgive us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.54,0:05:22.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.21,0:05:24.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's his fault for looking so scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.80,0:05:29.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Sayuri, are you really sure you want to marry him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.15,0:05:32.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I have young men with plenty of backbone working for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.77,0:05:35.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! What are you\Nsaying at a time like this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.10,0:05:36.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.52,0:05:39.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really now! You always have to treat me like a child, don't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.66,0:05:42.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph. You are a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.46,0:05:45.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You still drink this sugary rubbish...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.59,0:05:48.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So what?! I like it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.86,0:05:50.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, how about saying something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.90,0:05:52.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at what your daughter is wearing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.20,0:06:00.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're beautiful. Though not nearly as beautiful as your late mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.83,0:06:04.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you ever give a normal compliment?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.58,0:06:09.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What beautiful roses!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.59,0:06:12.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Umemiya-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.43,0:06:14.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's he?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.21,0:06:18.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't remember? That's Umemiya-san; he was one year ahead of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.74,0:06:27.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Lemon tea suits you well, Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.05,0:06:28.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.67,0:06:30.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Today is a real disappointment for me.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:32.70,0:06:36.00,Character Card,,0055,0000,0060,,{\fad(400,0)}{\fs36}Atsushi Umemiya (18)\N{\fs30}Former class president\N of Teitan Middle School
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.70,0:06:36.00,Character Card,,0000,0000,0050,,{\fad(0,0)\fscx98.75\fscy147.5\c&HBD4951&\clip(313,545,663,678)}m 0 0 l -36 0 l -36 0 l -36 11 l -36 13 l 0 13 m -22 -11 m -44 -35
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.70,0:06:36.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:30.49,0:06:33.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I always believed that only I...
Dialogue: 2,0:06:33.62,0:06:36.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...could ever make you happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.00,0:06:38.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Umemiya-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.24,0:06:41.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.21,0:06:44.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a conceited jerk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.66,0:06:50.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! The battery's almost dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.05,0:06:51.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.82,0:06:54.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't there an electronics store near here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.06,0:06:58.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be back soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.17,0:06:59.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.73,0:07:03.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, you'd think to at least check that before leaving the house...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.58,0:07:10.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You look exactly like Kudo Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.48,0:07:13.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just looking at your face makes me want to pinch you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.99,0:07:15.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.71,0:07:21.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, Kudo-kun looked just like my very first boyfriend...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.42,0:07:25.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His family ran the neighborhood candy store,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.04,0:07:28.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and whenever someone was bullying me, he'd always come to my rescue!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.38,0:07:35.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He would always secretly steal my favorite drink from his own store and give it to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.95,0:07:39.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Warm lemon tea!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.43,0:07:45.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Unable to forget those memories, I still drink it all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.23,0:07:47.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like it gives me courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.72,0:07:52.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So he was the reason I was tormented for three long years?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.39,0:07:55.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So does he still live there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.78,0:08:01.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. One day, he suddenly moved away, and I've never seen him since.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.01,0:08:03.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's more to this story...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.65,0:08:07.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what're you being so shy about? You're the groom!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.18,0:08:10.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Toshihiko-san!
Dialogue: 1,0:08:10.01,0:08:12.76,Character Card,,0110,0000,0075,,{\fad(400,0)}{\fs36}Takasugi Toshihiko (28)\N{\fs30}Heir to the Takasugi Group
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.01,0:08:12.76,Character Card,,0000,0000,0050,,{\fad(0,0)\fscx98.75\fscy147.5\c&HBD4951&\clip(349,547,678,673)}m 0 0 l -36 0 l -36 0 l -36 11 l -36 13 l 0 13 m -22 -11 m -44 -35
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.01,0:08:12.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:10.50,0:08:12.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You look stunning, Sayuri!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.76,0:08:15.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is just our little secret, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.79,0:08:21.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you still drinking this cheap filth?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.15,0:08:22.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.13,0:08:28.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! You're the heir to the Takasugi Group!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.86,0:08:31.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! You're one of those Suzuki plutocrats!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.23,0:08:32.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.97,0:08:35.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see him at parties all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.24,0:08:37.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's indecisive and undependable,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.74,0:08:40.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and people say that the Takasugi family's going to end with him...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.58,0:08:50.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did that come from all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.21,0:08:54.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But she's with him,\Nso I think he'll be all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.52,0:08:58.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to interrupt, but it's almost time for the ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.39,0:08:59.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.64,0:09:04.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Go on ahead, Toshihiko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.00,0:09:08.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, I'll be there soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.15,0:09:10.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.07,0:09:18.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how's the bride?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.32,0:09:20.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Way to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.92,0:09:29.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that sound?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.67,0:09:31.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It came from her room!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.80,0:09:34.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei! Sensei! Sen...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.70,0:09:46.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem that sodium hydroxide was mixed in with the lemon tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.44,0:09:49.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So she drank it and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.40,0:09:53.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? There's something\Nfloating in the lemon tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.42,0:10:00.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a capsule!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.03,0:10:01.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.19,0:10:08.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So the perpetrator filled this capsule with sodium hydroxide,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.36,0:10:10.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then slipped it into the lemon tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.70,0:10:13.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, then it would take time for the poison to be released,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.87,0:10:16.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,making it impossible to determine when the crime was committed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.13,0:10:20.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, any one of you six who entered her room...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.98,0:10:24.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...could have poisoned the tea!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.43,0:10:27.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious!\NDoes that make me a suspect too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.14,0:10:29.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.02,0:10:31.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Have the capsule analyzed at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.57,0:10:35.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say. How come\Nyou're not counting him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.49,0:10:38.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure he entered the room too...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.90,0:10:42.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on now, a police superintendent would never poison his own daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.66,0:10:48.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the boy's right. I'm a suspect just as much as the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.08,0:10:49.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You do have a point...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.74,0:10:52.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,\Nwe were recording a video!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.63,0:10:53.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.29,0:10:56.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right! Did we\Nleave it on when we left?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.71,0:11:02.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The crime might've been caught on film!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.99,0:11:11.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.19,0:11:14.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You still drink this sugary rubbish...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.13,0:11:19.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...that only I could ever make you happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.07,0:11:22.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you still drinking this cheap filth?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.53,0:11:25.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like the actual poisoning wasn't caught on tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.54,0:11:31.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Though the video shows that nearly everyone touched the can at least once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.12,0:11:35.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning that everyone had the chance to poison the drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.58,0:11:42.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if Sensei's surgery is over...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.45,0:11:46.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Poisoning her favorite\Nlemon tea... how horrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.25,0:11:48.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Lemon tea, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.84,0:11:53.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Every time Sayuri drinks it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.32,0:11:56.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm reminded of a little girl I liked a lot a long time ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.33,0:11:59.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She always drank it with such happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.30,0:12:01.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but I never even knew her name...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.93,0:12:03.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, he couldn't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.01,0:12:08.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector. The results of\Nthe analysis have come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.46,0:12:13.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First, assuming the capsule was added to the lemon tea,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.06,0:12:16.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it would apparently take 15 to 16 minutes for it to dissolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.13,0:12:22.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the poison was added\Nat least 15 minutes before she collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.19,0:12:26.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was 1:46 when Ran-kun called the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.55,0:12:29.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming she collapsed to the floor one minute earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.40,0:12:32.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then that means the\Npoison was added before 1:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.64,0:12:36.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was exactly 1:30 when\NSuperintendent Matsumoto left.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.61,0:12:37.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.38,0:12:43.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This rules out both the groom and myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.13,0:12:46.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We came to see Sensei after he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.16,0:12:49.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We found something strange about the poisoned can...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.66,0:12:53.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The superintendent's fingerprints aren't anywhere on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.62,0:12:57.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You fool!\NWhat are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.42,0:12:59.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As you can clearly see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.83,0:13:01.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...I had the can in my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.71,0:13:03.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you make a thorough check?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.88,0:13:05.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.43,0:13:07.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.77,0:13:13.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! The battery's almost dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.78,0:13:15.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.31,0:13:20.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.30,0:13:23.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!\NWhen Sonoko left...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.32,0:13:25.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...she didn't have her can with her!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.15,0:13:26.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where in the world did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.99,0:13:30.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.08,0:13:35.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me that she drank from...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.65,0:13:40.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, mister. Were the superintendent's fingerprints the only ones missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.94,0:13:44.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that Umemiya\Nperson's weren't on it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.09,0:13:46.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured as much!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.05,0:13:49.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, where\Ndid that capsule come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.34,0:13:52.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! I've figured\Nout the culprit's intention!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.12,0:13:54.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know the truth behind that capsule!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.82,0:13:58.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector. I found this\Nin a trashcan in the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.44,0:14:00.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A glass jar...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.33,0:14:02.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That looks like sodium hydroxide inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.94,0:14:04.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sodium hydroxide?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.28,0:14:08.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This could be the container the\Nperpetrator used when poisoning the tea!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.24,0:14:09.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.74,0:14:11.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sodium hydroxide is a dangerous chemical
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.53,0:14:15.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that absorbs water in the air and turns into a liquid in mere minutes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.61,0:14:17.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Send this for analysis too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.48,0:14:19.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've figured it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.91,0:14:24.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was that person who smeared her dress with blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.12,0:14:30.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.42,0:14:33.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We want to see Sensei\Nat the hospital right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.26,0:14:36.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on a little longer! We're not finished with our investigation!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.61,0:14:40.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle Mouri isn't around today, so I'll need a pinch hitter!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.07,0:14:49.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now to match this voice\Nchanger to Sonoko's voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.40,0:14:51.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko?\NWhat's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.36,0:14:54.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.23,0:14:57.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know the identity of the one who\Npoisoned Matsumoto-sensei's lemon tea!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.75,0:15:00.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You... You have, Sonoko-kun?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.75,0:15:07.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said that the perpetrator put the poison capsule in her tea 15 minutes before she collapsed, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.71,0:15:12.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, because it would take 15 to 16 minutes for the capsule to dissolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.68,0:15:17.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's assuming the poison was really in that capsule.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.50,0:15:23.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All we're sure of is that the capsule was floating in the poisoned lemon tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.11,0:15:24.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're saying that the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.61,0:15:29.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The poison and the capsule were added in separately,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.11,0:15:35.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to fool us into thinking that the poison was added at least 15 minutes prior.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.20,0:15:40.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's true, then you two could have done it as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.86,0:15:44.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on. Everything she's\Nsaying is pure conjecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.17,0:15:47.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It really might have\Nbeen a poison capsule.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.57,0:15:48.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.63,0:15:51.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is not conjecture as there is proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.93,0:15:53.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In the video that Ran taped.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.76,0:16:01.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector. Take a close look at the can of lemon tea on the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.61,0:16:07.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.45,0:16:20.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The labels are facing different directions!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.87,0:16:25.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran. Do you remember where I put my lemon tea when this happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.37,0:16:26.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.13,0:16:30.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were in a hurry so\Nyou put it on the table...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.90,0:16:33.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It couldn't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.09,0:16:35.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that your can?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.51,0:16:38.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.60,0:16:42.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason it looks like there's only one can\Nis because the two cans are perfectly lined up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.89,0:16:49.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She took my can, which\Njust happened to be in front!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.94,0:16:55.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As proof of this, the poisoned can was devoid of the fingerprints of the superintendent and Umemiya-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.15,0:16:58.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,even though they clearly\Nhad held the can earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.10,0:17:01.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd bet that my fingerprints are on it, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.37,0:17:03.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's exactly right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.38,0:17:04.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.33,0:17:09.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...that some time between my daughter taking the wrong can and collapsing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.35,0:17:12.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,someone put the poison and the capsule in separately.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.30,0:17:17.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. And the only ones with her at the time were Conan-kun and Takasugi-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.46,0:17:19.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,not to mention me and Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.89,0:17:22.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Excluding Conan-kun,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.22,0:17:24.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when Ran and I returned from buying batteries,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.88,0:17:28.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Takasugi-san was holding the can and then she took it from him,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.39,0:17:30.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so it would've been impossible for me or Ran to poison it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.65,0:17:34.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So he's the only one left?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.11,0:17:36.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. There's one other person.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.47,0:17:38.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, herself!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.57,0:17:40.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mean... suicide?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.53,0:17:44.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But if she did mix the\Npoison in to kill herself,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.58,0:17:47.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,she would've added it shortly before collapsing to the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.04,0:17:49.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And to do that,\Nshe would need two things.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.75,0:17:52.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,An airtight container and a desiccant!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.71,0:17:58.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It takes only a few minutes for sodium hydroxide to turn to liquid when exposed to the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.95,0:18:01.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was in this room the entire time,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.51,0:18:05.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so she would have needed\Na container to safely store it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.93,0:18:08.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the container was found...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.40,0:18:11.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...in a trashcan in the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.27,0:18:17.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is proof that someone other than\NSensei brought the poison into this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.52,0:18:21.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the only one who could've slipped the poison into the lemon tea...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.74,0:18:25.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...was you, Takasugi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.58,0:18:28.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Toshihiko! How could you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.40,0:18:33.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Why'd you do\Nthat to my daughter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.70,0:18:36.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you wanna know\Nso badly, then I'll tell you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.92,0:18:39.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It all started 20 years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.19,0:18:44.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When a car that you were chasing ran over my mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.23,0:18:53.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom! Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.97,0:18:53.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My mother was still alive at the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.69,0:18:56.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She could've survived if you had rushed her to the hospital in your car!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.65,0:18:58.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But instead...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.17,0:18:59.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in the way! Get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.61,0:19:05.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,15 minutes later,\Nmy mother died, lying on the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.79,0:19:11.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,From that day forth, I never once forgot your cruel, heartless face!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.96,0:19:14.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he telling the truth, superintendent?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.65,0:19:18.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I didn't see her; she was\Nobscured by the car's shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.64,0:19:22.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Later on, I learned of the accident and rushed to his house,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.39,0:19:24.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he had already moved out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.91,0:19:29.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My mother was the only family I had.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.26,0:19:33.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was adopted by the Takasugi family as they had no children of their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.01,0:19:37.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then seven years ago, Kazumi brought a girl with her!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.61,0:19:41.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! The instant I learned that she was your daughter,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.72,0:19:45.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,my nearly-forgotten flames of revenge roared back to life!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.58,0:19:51.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why didn't you...\Nwhy didn't you kill me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.04,0:19:57.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you died, you wouldn't get to experience how heartbreaking it is to lose someone dear to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.22,0:20:02.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was one stupid girl, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.90,0:20:05.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She had no clue I was getting close to her to get revenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.67,0:20:09.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Though I'm sure being the heir to the Takasugi fortune was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.80,0:20:14.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who\Ndoesn't have a clue, Toshihiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.22,0:20:14.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.90,0:20:17.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sayuri knew everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.83,0:20:20.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even about the accident 20 years ago and your lineage!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.82,0:20:23.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you're lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.93,0:20:27.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She'd never marry me\Nif she knew who I really was!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.07,0:20:29.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You still don't get it, even after seeing all that lemon tea she drinks?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.88,0:20:33.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the first boyfriend that she's always been thinking about
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.98,0:20:35.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,for the past 20 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.47,0:20:43.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sayuri kept talking about how much you looked like him, so I did some investigating and found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.63,0:20:48.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was really worried, even after she accepted your proposal...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.05,0:20:52.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't know what to do to earn your forgiveness...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.44,0:20:57.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, you... you went and...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.02,0:21:01.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me she saw\Nhim poison the drink?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.60,0:21:05.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She knew it was poisoned?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.97,0:21:08.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, I'll be there soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.24,0:21:11.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.75,0:21:15.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Superintendent! We just received word from the hospital!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.75,0:21:20.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's been upgraded to stable condition!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.02,0:21:26.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is great!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.76,0:21:28.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.01,0:22:58.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Two months later, Sensei\Nchecked out of the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.63,0:23:01.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's great that you got to leave the hospital earlier than expected!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.97,0:23:04.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And I hear that Toshihiko-san's sentence was reduced...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.48,0:23:08.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I did drink the\Npoison on my own free will...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.29,0:23:11.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But in the end, it looks like I only\Nsucceeded in getting him in trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.21,0:23:14.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet he hates me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.41,0:23:17.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, Sensei! Cheer up!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.85,0:23:20.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In celebration of leaving\Nthe hospital, I'll buy you a drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.25,0:23:21.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.87,0:23:23.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.76,0:23:32.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...lemon tea, it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.10,0:23:38.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's important to cherish\Nmemories of the past!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.44,0:23:43.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Really now! If you keep this up, you'll never get married!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.06,0:23:47.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But she was married three years later...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.60,0:23:53.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Married to the one she had thought about for 20 long years, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.92,0:24:08.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing of the sort!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.29,0:24:11.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way you could possibly be the murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.15,0:24:13.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.92,0:24:19.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were the one who just explained why she couldn't have done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.60,0:24:21.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! Now I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.60,0:24:24.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an alibi trick involving elevators!
